Package de.wwu.muggl.vm.execution

Provides algorithms needed during the execution and other execution related classes.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
ExecutionAlgorithms This class provided basic algorithms specified by the java virtual machine specification.
MugglToJavaConversion This class provides for the conversion of objects from the java virtual machine implementation of SUN to the jvm of Muggl and the other way around.
NativeWrapper This class provides the functionality to wrap native methods calls.
ResolutionAlgorithms This class provided basic algorithms specified by the java virtual machine specification.
 

Exception Summary
ConversionException Exception that is to be If the conversion of objects from the java virtual machine implementation of SUN to the jvm of Muggl or the other way around failed.
ExecutionException Exception that is to be thrown on problems while Executing java bytecode in the normal execution mode.
ForwardingUnsuccessfulException Exception that is to be thrown when the forwarding of a native invocation was not successful.
 

Package de.wwu.muggl.vm.execution Description

Provides algorithms needed during the execution and other execution related classes. Beside the execution and resolution algorithm a native wrapper is provided. If offers wrapping functionality in different ways and enables a processing of native methods. (Native methods are not present as classfiles, but as plattform-specific, "native" implementations.)

Author:
Tim Majchrzak
